cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DS, cs.DB

The paper discusses a data mining algorithm for discovering frequent serial episodes in sequential data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The paper also presents a novel application of this algorithm in text classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves statistical modeling and analysis, which suggests the possibility of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) as potential sub-categories.
